About Us

At Biointelect, we partner with innovators across the life sciences ecosystem including early‑stage Biotech and MedTech companies, Multinational pharmaceutical companies, universities, research institutes, government bodies, and not‑for‑profits. We deliver high‑quality consulting services, are a full service Clinical Research Organisation (CRO) and support organisations working to improve health outcomes in Australia and globally.

Opportunity

We are looking for a Business Operations Manager who enjoys practical, day‑to‑day operational work and supporting the financial and systems foundations of a busy consulting business. This role suits someone with a solid grounding in business analytics (particularly CRM related), finance or operations who is ready to take ownership of core processes, maintain reliable business systems, proactively enable our business metric analytics and contribute to ongoing company development.

You will partner closely with the CEO, Leadership Team, across our team of consultants, and our partners in finance and SalesForce (CRM) to ensure accurate reporting, smooth operational workflows, and consistent data management across Biointelect and the Biointelect Venturer incubator program. This is a hands‑on role with variety and structure, ideal for someone who wants to grow their capability in a supportive environment.

Key Responsibilities

Build and manage dashboards, KPIs, and data insights to support internal decision making
Support monthly financial reporting, forecasting, and analytics in partnership with the Finance business partner
Assist with developing and maintaining financial and operational SOPs and governance documentation

In collaboration with the Quality Manager, coordinate compliance activities, internal controls, and audit preparation

Assist the CEO and Leadership Team with reporting, process mapping, and general operational tasks
Contribute to ongoing process improvements across SalesForce, finance, systems, and internal workflows

Essential Requirements

Tertiary qualification in Finance, Accounting, Business Analytics or a related field
Three to five years of experience in business analytics, finance, or operations
Strong experience with CRM systems, ideally Salesforce
Experience developing dashboards and KPI reporting
High proficiency in Excel and financial modelling
Clear and confident communication skills with the ability to work effectively with internal and external stakeholders
Agility to work across multiple projects and in a dynamic environment
Strong organisational skills, attention to detail, and the ability to manage multiple tasks
Experience supporting governance, compliance, or audit processes

Desirable Requirements

Experience in an operations role or professional services environment
Understanding of clinical trials financial processes

Why Join Us?

At Biointelect, you will be part of a purpose‑driven team contributing to meaningful work in health and life sciences. You will gain exposure to a wide range of projects, learn from experienced colleagues, and build your operational and financial capability in a supportive environment.

If this sounds like you, we welcome your application. Apply now to take the next step in your operations and finance career.

Please include your resume and a brief cover letter outlining your suitability for the role.

Biointelect is an equal opportunity employer. All applicants will be considered for employment without attention to race, colour, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran, or disability status.

About the role

The AI Enablement Lead is a strategic leadership role responsible for driving responsible and effective AI adoption across the organisation.

This role will lead the design, delivery, and governance of AI solutions, manage the AI innovation pipeline from ideation through to production, and build organisational capability through training, guidance, and communities of practice.

The role is also tasked with logging and tracking tickets through the ITSM system, ensuring issues are promptly addressed and resolved within the agreed SLAs, maintaining accurate documentation, adhering to IT Policies and Procedures, ensuring compliance with Health and Safety regulations and following Security Best Practices. The support Officer will provide recommendations for new technologies that could benefit the business.

Key responsibilities include (but are not limited to):

AI Strategy and Governance

Establish and maintain enterprise AI principles, policies, standards, and guidelines in collaboration with QSA and Quanta stakeholders

Own the risk assessment process for proposed AI solutions and use cases.

Define guardrails and controls to ensure AI solutions are developed and deployed safely, responsibly and meet quality standards

Collaborate with legal, risk, and compliance teams to ensure AI initiatives meet regulatory requirements and organisational policies.

Monitor emerging AI regulations and standards. Adapt governance frameworks accordingly

Establish metrics and reporting mechanisms to track AI adoption, value delivery, and governance compliance.

AI Solution Design & Delivery

Lead the design and delivery of AI solutions aligned to business priorities and strategic objectives.

Ensure AI solutions integrate with enterprise architecture, data architecture, and technology standards.

Collaborate with data teams to ensure AI solutions are built on trusted, quality data foundations.

Define solution architectures for AI applications, considering scalability, performance, security and maintainability.

AI Innovation Pipeline Management

Manage the enterprise AI innovation pipeline, from ideation and use case identification through pilot and production deployment.

Establish processes for capturing, evaluating, and prioritising AI opportunities across the QSA business

Facilitate workshops and innovation sessions with business stakeholders to identify high-value AI use cases.

Develop business cases for AI initiatives, including value assessment, feasibility analysis, and resource requirements.

Oversee pilot programs and proof-of-concepts, establishing success criteria and evaluation frameworks

AI Enablement and Engagement

Develop training programs and materials to build AI literacy and capability across the organisation.

Design and deliver presentations, workshops, and training sessions to QSA staff and stakeholder groups.

Create practical guidance, playbooks, and toolkits to support responsible AI adoption and development.

Establish and facilitate communities of practice for AI practitioners, business analysts, and stakeholders.




To be successful in this role, you will have;

7-10 years of experience in technology roles, with at least 3-5 years focused on AI/ML solutions, data science, or AI strategy.

Demonstrated experience in designing, implementing, and governing AI solutions in enterprise environments.

Strong knowledge of AI platforms and tools (e.g., Azure AI, AWS AI/ML services, Google Cloud AI, enterprise AI platforms).

Understanding of data architecture, data governance, and data quality principles as they relate to AI.

Experience with AI risk assessment methodologies and governance frameworks.

Understanding of enterprise architecture principles and integration patterns.

Familiarity with cloud platforms and modern technology architectures.

Knowledge of cybersecurity, privacy, and compliance considerations for AI systems.

Proven leadership skills with the ability to influence and drive change across an organization.

Strong  communication and presentation skills, with the ability to explain complex AI concepts to diverse audiences.

Strong stakeholder management capabilities, including experience working with executive leadership and governance committees.

Demonstrated ability to develop and deliver training programs and capability building initiatives.

Strategic thinking with the ability to align AI initiatives with business objectives.

Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with a data-driven approach to decision-making.

Experience managing innovation pipelines and driving value from emerging technologies.

Excellent facilitation skills for workshops, working groups, and communities of practice.

Project and program management capabilities with experience delivering complex initiatives.

Change management expertise with experience leading organizational transformation.

Willingness to travel to various Operating Unites around Australia.

Drive operational and commercial excellence.

Identify and develop exceptional employees.

Overview


Microsoft Advertising is a global leader in digital advertising, helping advertisers grow through search, display, video, and retail media solutions. We are seeking a Head of Analytical Leads to lead a high‑performing team that turns data into measurable business impact.

In this role, you will manage a team of senior analytical leaders across APAC, delivering insights and recommendations that improve client performance and unlock new investment opportunities on the Microsoft Advertising platform. You will combine industry knowledge, digital marketing expertise, and advanced analytics to craft compelling, data‑driven narratives that influence senior decision‑makers through clear storytelling and visualisation.

The ideal candidate brings strong people leadership, analytical and consulting capabilities, and a proactive, challenger mindset, with the ability to partner effectively across teams and markets.

At Microsoft, our mission is to empower every person and organisation to achieve more. We operate with a growth mindset, act with integrity and accountability, and foster an inclusive culture where everyone can thrive.

Work model: From 26 January 2026, Microsoft AI employees living within 25 miles of a non‑U.S. office are expected to work onsite at least four days per week, subject to local laws.

Responsibilities

People Management: Managers deliver success through empowerment and accountability by modeling, coaching, and caring. Model: Live our culture. Embody our values. Practice our leadership principles. Coach: Define team objectives and outcomes. Enable success across boundaries. Help the team adapt and learn. Care: Attract and retain great people. Know each individual’s capabilities and aspirations. Invest in the growth of others.

Application of Data: Ensures team members evaluate the sufficiency of data between internal and external sources, drives accountability of identification and resolution of data quality issues, and encourages and coordinates cross-team collaboration and data sharing to build data pipelines or integrations. Leverages data, analyses, and learnings to articulate industry- and client-relevant stories and insights to various audiences and at industry events.

Data Analysis: Builds best practices for team members to leverage and apply their expertise across client and business-related analytical needs. Guides and coaches team members through the execution of complex analyses to resolve analytical challenges, interpret results within a client context, and acts on opportunities with actionable recommendations. Supervises team's data analyses, feedback, and that recommendations are accessible and easily understood by the relevant stakeholder groups, and ensures accountability and efficiency in delivering outcomes that are aligned with client, industry, and business needs.

Data Privacy and Governance: Contributes knowledge across the team in data privacy and governance rules and regulations and guides others to uphold and apply updated data privacy and governance, maintain awareness of where to seek further expertise on such rules and regulations when needed, and leverage personal expertise to identify and share relevant best practices. Identifies appropriate internal and/or external stakeholders to update or improve data privacy and governance practices to better align to industry.

Improvement, Efficiency, and Innovation: Guides the team to develop and implement methods that create systematic efficiencies in core work related to analytics and reporting that are reusable, readily discoverable, self-service, and directed to meaningful interpretation of data that drive impactful business decisions across the organization. Coaches team in guiding optimal and innovative methods for operationalizing, sharing, and scaling insights, and coordinates automation of patterns of ad hoc analyses into regular reporting features. Shares thought leadership and partners with leaders to leverage and implement automated methods for use in data collection, reporting, and analysis, while contributing to operational tracking to ensure work actions and decisions are appropriately measured.

Orchestration and Collaboration: Establishes and leverages strategic working relationships within and across internal and client teams to ensure data sources, methodologies, models, and analytical tools and processes are high-quality, and that recommendations are data-driven and appropriately relevant to clients' industry vertical(s) to consistently drive positive impact. Guides own and team's actions across networks of peers and client stakeholders to leverage resources and solutions that were instrumental to success in similar contexts, and shares expertise on industry vertical, clients, and competitors across teams to inform decision-making related to advanced analyses and their interpretations.

Presentation of Results: Provides guidance to team members on the development and delivery of compelling and easily understood client-facing presentations of analyses, reports, data visualizations, etc. Provides guidance to team members on how to synthesize insights into a story, and proactively leverages stories to influence leadership and other senior stakeholders' decision-making and drives business outcomes internally, externally, and within industry verticals. Supports efforts to improve efficiency of reporting and presentations, and encourages others to share insights and build presentations that are accessible, that cultivate trust with clients, and that present relevant information accurately, clearly, and appropriately to influence decision-making for intended audience(s).

Understanding Client's Business: Advances own and team's comprehensive understanding of clients' business knowledge, including industry trends, clients' value propositions, and the competitive landscape to help drive sustainable long-term value over competitor's solutions, address the most impactful business needs, and adapt to anticipated industry trends. Identifies the appropriate scope and impact to develop solutions, builds and leverages connections with client's leadership, and includes appropriate stakeholders in scoping process. Coaches and encourages team members to broaden knowledge of clients' business and industry verticals.

Qualifications

Required Qualifications:

8+ years experience in statistics, mathematics, analytics, data science, data analysis and reporting, business intelligence, business and financial analysis, or related field; OR equivalent experience 8+ years experience using tools such as PowerBI/Tableau, DAX, R, SQL for data manipulation and visualization on large datasets.

2+ years people management experience.

Experience in the APAC Market including Australia, Japan, and China

Experience communicating complex analyses to a mix of both technical and non-technical partners and clients.

Experience utilizing analytical tools to turn massive, dynamic datasets into actionable insights.

Experience pairing data visualization with storytelling to deliver persuasive presentations that influence varying audience levels.

Experience conducting, interpreting, and clearly communicating measurement analyses (e.g., incrementality, attribution, lift studies) to inform client decisions.

Experience and proficiency using PowerBI/Tableau, DAX, SQL for data manipulation and visualization. Working knowledge and familiarity in a combination of the following data manipulation and visualization tools is a plus: Python, R, PowerPivot, Microsoft Advertising API.

Working knowledge of statistics, predictive modeling and data clustering/classification techniques.

Preferred Qualifications:

Experience in a partner or account management/client service/client-facing role.

Experience in digital media, data analysis, and data management.

Job Description

The Role  

Working with highly motivated product teams and reporting within a dedicated team of Experimentation data scientists, you will be responsible for understanding the value drivers of our key global services/products, assessing their performance, and identifying improvement opportunities through rigorous analysis and the design, execution and interpretation of experiments. 

The ideal candidate has a strong grasp of statistical concepts and experimental design and can succinctly explain those concepts to non-technical audiences. You are comfortable working with large, complex datasets and analytical tools, and partnering with engineering and platform teams to ensure experiments are reliably measured within our best-in-class experimentation platform. You collaborate closely across functions to deliver trustworthy, actionable insights that help teams make evidence-based decisions. 

Equally, you are comfortable operating in ambiguous situations and can determine and apply appropriate analytical and experimental techniques to solve problems. 

As the leading employment marketplace in APAC, we believe we offer a unique value proposition to purpose-driven candidates for a role of this nature: the product innovation and marketplace improvements that you help SEEK to measure and evaluate will translate to millions of additional people finding jobs that they otherwise may not have found. We believe few other companies offer the opportunity to make such a tangible and positive difference at this scale. 

Key Responsibilities 

Understanding Service/Product value drivers  

Develop knowledge of use cases, user behaviours & segmentation and service mechanics (algorithms and models) across our SEEK Group partner sites and countries  

Run experiments and support the improvement of the experiment framework  

Work with guidance from senior colleagues to devise techniques and frameworks to ensure automated algorithms optimisation (multi-arm bandits and similar)  

Assist in driving continuous improvement of experimentation framework in scale, languages, speed of experiment and quality of insight by choosing appropriate techniques (A/B testing, interleaving, Bayesian methods)  

Work with engineers to improve and automate data collection and testing framework  

Analyse experiments and drive product improvement  

Design experiments that appropriately address hypotheses and will lead to trustworthy learning. 

Test hypotheses and analyse results, segmenting where required to surface insights from experiments  

Articulate findings and communicate recommendations back to the senior team and business stakeholders  

The Team  

You’ll report to SEEK’s Head of Experimentation and collaborate daily with: 

Peers: Product Managers, Data Scientists, Data Engineers, Analysts 

Key Partners: AI Platform Services, Product Analytics, Product Management 

Together, you’ll continue building SEEK’s evolving SEEK’s experimentation capabilities — enabling faster, more confident decision-making across the business. 

Qualifications

You are autonomous, intellectually curious and intrinsically motivated to solve ambiguous problems and drive to an outcome. You love a challenge, and appreciate working with smart, motivated peers to make an impact.  

Background in Data Science, Engineering, Statistics, Econometrics or a discipline that makes substantial use of these disciplines. (e.g. Bioinformatics). 

Experience with data pipeline technologies, demonstrating the ability to design, implement, and maintain efficient and scalable data processing workflows. 

Strong Python and SQL skills are required, along with exposure to Databricks, PySpark, Airflow, and Kubernetes. 

Foundational knowledge of hypothesis testing and associated statistical techniques. 

Advanced analytical and problem-solving skills. 

Developing (or demonstrating) the ability to translate and present data in a concise and meaningful way to stakeholders. 

Proven ability to independently work with various stakeholder groups – data science, engineering, business stakeholders. 

Additional information 

Influencing and interpersonal skills  

Excellent organisational skills, including the use of Agile practices  

An ability and motivation to ‘pitch in’ and do what needs to be done to get the right outcome in a small team 

 

Additional Information
